  "texts": [
    "In contrast, the 1D RCE model, which lacks explicit photochemical loss terms, maintains HCN primarily through hydrogenation and CN recombination, likely leading to an overestimation of HCN abundance in this region.",
    "NH 3 is photodissociated through NH 3 + h𝜈 → NH 2 + H in all three models.",
    "Despite this loss, NH 3 is partially replenished through NH 2 + H 2 → NH 3 + H, though the efficiency of this recycling varies.",
    "On the west limb, minor contributions arise from the reverse reaction NH 3 + CH → NH 2 + CH 2, while in the 1D model, the reverse of NH 3 + OH → NH 2 + H 2 O also plays a role.",
    "The net result is a decline in NH 3 abundance with altitude in all models, although the magnitude of depletion differs due to the interplay between photochemistry and vertical mixing."
